<br>
Over 60% of this country is overweight, over 40% of the 60% are morbidly obese. It is due to many factors, parents not cooking enough anymore or buying premade or prepackaged food. Also it is due to the &quot;supersize&quot; craze... Current studies show people are taking the indulgance and portion sizes of restaurants home with them, and that is a BAD thing. Fact is, your average restaurant meal contains enough calories for an ENTIRE DAY. Taking that home 3 meals a day is one of the causes of the alarming rise in overweight people, especially children.<br>
<br>
We have a generation now becoming parents, who were raised without the proper nutritional background, many who cant cook and eat out 4-5 times a week. Many schools now have vending machines in the cafeteria, when I was a kid you couldnt get snack foods during lunch, it wasnt allowed. <br>
<br>
So now, people seeing themselves and their little ones puffing up like bags of Orville Redenbocker start making excuses, saying things like they &quot;eat right&quot; Hell, if the average american saw what &quot;eating right&quot; means I'm sure a majority of us would find ourselves in the wrong. Truth is people have been led in all sorts of false directions by weight loss claims and fad diets. That, mixed with good old fashioned american overindulgance, laziness, and gluttony are responsible for a generation of people suing left and right because they cant sit in a stadium seat, cant put on their seatbelt, and didnt know McDonalds was BAD for them T.T.T.T<br>
<br>
Nothing makes me angrier than Fat people who feel the world owes them something because of something they have done to themselves. It's a sickening attitude to have.<br>
<br>
As for not being able to exercise, thats not true unless you are a quadrapallegic(sp?) And even then, @#%$, Bruce Lee rehabillitated himself from a vegetable with every muscle in his body atrophied from paralysis back into a fighting machine. Guys in wheelchairs play basketball, there is no excuse for anyone short of someone with no physical limbs.<br>
