<br>
In the end it comes down to 2 things, either you are motivated or you are not (lazy). It's much easier to sit on your ass eating cheetos than to actually do something about it. Take it from someone who knows, sometimes you have to make big sacrafices in order to get something done. So the skinny people at the gym make fun of you, big @#%$ deal, get a walkman and you wont hear @#%$, concentrate on what you are supposed to be doing there and you wont notice them pointing at you. It's very convenient to blame others' actions but not always legit. It's not that hard to ignore someone you dont even KNOW when they are making fun of you, who gives a @#%$...<br>
